title: Break Expectations and Be Unremarkable
author: Sarah Overmyer
tags: queer, feminisim, religion, social
desc: We all have silent expectations about the way things are. It doesn't mean it's bad when those expectations are violated; heck, we may want them broken. But it does mean they're there, lingering in the backs of our minds. Things don't jump out when they're unremarkable.
